  "prompt": "Is Kyiv (Kiev) radioactive?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, Kyiv itself is not considered to be significantly radioactive. Most of the radiation concerns in Ukraine are related to the Chernobyl disaster, which occurred in 1986. The Chernobyl Exclusion Zone, located approximately 100 kilometers (about 62 miles) north of Kyiv, is a highly contaminated area due to the release of radioactive materials during the accident. \n\nWhile there may be increased radiation levels in certain areas close to the Exclusion Zone, Kyiv has not shown high levels of radioactivity in general. However, it's always good to refer to the latest data from authoritative sources, such as government agencies or environmental organizations, for the most current information on radiation levels.",
